This paper is primarily focused on the development of intelligent software agents for cyber defense, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and the challenges of implementing such agents in a complex system (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper addresses the need for these agents to operate autonomously (cs.SY) and the potential impact on network infrastructure (cs.NI).
